g.text: Vision: envisioning an unconstrained and ambitious long-term future.
We use it to align many teams without central control.
It is illustrative and directional. We want as few as possible.
Strategy: There will be many specific challenges to moving from the present
to an aspirational future. Strategies approach them. They are practical, accurate,
and detailed. We want as many as useful.
Epic: the actual projects that will change the state of the present world to shift
it to where we want to be.
Where do visions come from, and how do they relate to what we do daily?
